Ok so my mom and I went to go donate our blood today.  I did good, I filled up my whole bag with out feeling dizzy or anything. Yay.  Then came the little viles...half way through the 3rd one I got dizzy, so I told the guy then on the fourth I told him I was going to puke.  Low and behold seconds later I doing it in a trash can, but they were a bit slow getting it to my mouth so LUCKY ME I got some on my Vines shirt. My mom made fun of me. Good job mom.

I went home to change after I drank fluids and stuff. My dad thought it was funny too. Lovely. I changed then we went to Target, and Honey Baked Ham. 

On the way to HBH(honey baked ham) my mom and I saw a guy on the side of the road but we couldn't tell if he was breathing, so we made a U-turn and pulled into someone's driveway.  My mom got out and shook him a bit, no response, so she looked for a pulse he was breathing, so we called 911. Meanwhile two other cars stopped to see what was going on and if we needed help. One pair were a doctor and nurse. They tried to get a reponse from no, no luck.  Two police cars came and one ambulance.  They did there stuff and we left.

On the way back there were two ambulances and one cop car and they had gotten the guy to wake up.

Well that was my exciting day.

I actually have to get up early tomorrow, but it's for a good reason.  My mom and I have our appointment to donate blood. This will be my second time, and hopefully I won't end up alomost passing out like I did last time!
